  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6802.62 trading 78 points below the flip strike at 6880, dealers are currently in long gamma mode and likely buying this dip while providing stabilizing flow. The massive +5.1B gamma wall at 6900 creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the -1.7B negative gamma pocket at 6755 forms a floor where dealers flip to buying. The recent GEX surge reinforces the PIN regime dynamics, with dealers acting as shock absorbers that should contain moves between 6755-6900.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect range-bound price action with upside capped near 6900 and downside supported around 6755.",
